description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Radiographer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a Bank Radiographer in our Shrewsbury Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are a small department, with a very friendly team and we are currently looking for a motivated Bank Radiographer to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Either you join us from the NHS or a private setting, you will find that we offer you an unrivalled opportunity to grow the respected career that you always wanted. You will benefit from using an X-Ray retrofit DR systemand our commitment to give you more time with partners. As a Radiographer you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a high-quality diagnostic imaging service for a very varied caseload – within the department, on the ward and in theatre.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have enough experience to be able to work independently and use your own professional judgement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with leading practitioners and experiencing new practices, equipment and facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing a service of the highest quality, delivered with sensitivity and compassion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; To succeed as a Bank Radiographer you will have;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High levels of technical knowledge and the ability to work quickly and accurately, with a great eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge regarding UK Rules and Regulations and able to show familiarity with regulatory compliance requirements regarding IRMER, GDPR, RIS &amp; PACS, Health &amp; Safety, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to take on a clinical workload at short notice is essential, after the standard induction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A caring nature – to see each patient as an individual and carry out this role with understanding and empathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A BSC degree in diagnostic radiography to meet the registration requirements of the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A postgraduate qualification in an area of specialization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post registration experience relevant to the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and team working abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to communicate effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt; As a Bank Worker you would be part of a pool of casual workers who would be called upon when required to provide cover during periods of sickness, holidays or increased workload. You would not be classified as an employee and would therefore have no fixed working pattern or entitlement to guaranteed or continuous employment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday in line with the Working Time Directive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our Pension Scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted gym membership at £15.00 a month that they need to set up directly with the club. Discount does not extend to partners and family members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - £16 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Shrewsbury&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Bank Contract &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post.’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
